com.acrolinx.javasdk.gui.sessions.controller.inline

Interface InlineCheckDocumentSessionController

  • All Superinterfaces:
    DocumentSessionController

    public interface InlineCheckDocumentSessionController
extends DocumentSessionController
    The interface InlineCheckDocumentSessionController is used for interaction with the Acrolinx Java SDK after an inline check was performed. It could be down casted to DocumentSessionController which is required for DocumentSessionControllerProvider.getDocumentSessionController().

      • setActiveMarkingAndShowPopup

        void setActiveMarkingAndShowPopup(Area locationOnScreen,
                                Key key,
                                GuiUpdateListener guiUpdateListener)
        Sets the active marking (highlighting it with the active color) and shows the context menu.
        Parameters:
        locationOnScreen - the location where the context menu should be displayed. This should be the mouse position.
        key - the key of the current marking for activation
        guiUpdateListener - This GuiUpdateListener will be used to notify the GUI to update after an action has been performed.

      • getMarkingController

        MarkingController getMarkingController()
        Gets the MarkingController used by this InlineCheckDocumentSessionController. Warning: Do not use this method unless you have good reasons to do.
